# Zero to running tool

Primary reference: `skills/zero-to-running-tool/SKILL.md`

Use this rule as a **gate** before any other unicore rule when:

- the user identifies as non-engineer (PM, finance, legal, ops, support)
- the user mentions a clean or new machine
- a prerequisite check (`node -v`, `gh auth status`, `railway whoami`) fails

Verify each step (Node 24, Colima, `gh` org membership, Railway workspace) before continuing. Do not silently move on past a failing check.
